# Testing Standards

- Test runner: Vitest; colocate tests next to source as `*.test.ts`
- Use descriptive test names that read as sentences
- Every package must have tests; the `@decade/matching-engine` package is held to
  a high bar — its tests encode every example in the engineering brief
- Run `pnpm test` (all) or `pnpm --filter @decade/<name> test` (one package)
- Keep the matching engine pure so it can be tested without a database or clock
